"Lets take a SQL table with 2 columns, which is composite primary key:\r\n\r\n```sql\r\nCREATE TABLE `blog_categ` (\r\n  `categ_id` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL,\r\n  `blog_id` int(10) unsigned NOT NULL,\r\n  PRIMARY KEY (`categ_id`,`blog_id`),\r\n)\r\n```\r\nExecuting model upsert:\r\n```php\r\nstatic::getDb()->createCommand()->upsert(static::tableName(), $values, true)->execute();\r\n```\r\nProduce incorrect SQL error with empty UPDATE list:\r\n```sql\r\nINSERT INTO `blog_categ` (`categ_id`, `blog_id`) VALUES (2244, 139) ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE\r\n```\r\nThe correct SQL will be:\r\n```sql\r\nINSERT INTO `blog_categ` (`categ_id`, `blog_id`) VALUES (2244, 139) ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE `categ_id`=`categ_id`\r\n```\r\nIf all columns are unique, then QueryBuilder::prepareUpsertColumns return empty list of $updateNames and produce incorrect sql.  So, when $updateNames is empty, the behavior must be the same as when $updateColumns = false.\r\n\r\nSmall fix to yii\\db\\mysql\\QueryBuilder::upsert($table, $insertColumns, $updateColumns, &$params)\r\n```php\r\n        --- } elseif ($updateColumns === false) {\r\n        +++ } elseif ($updateColumns === false || empty($updateNames)) { \r\n```\r\nPlease, add this fix.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n| Q                | A\r\n| ---------------- | ---\r\n| Yii version      | 2.0.24\r\n| PHP version      | \r\n| Operating system |\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"samdark","id":47294,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ3Mjk0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/47294?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/samdark","html_url":"https://github.com/samdark","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samdark/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samdark/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samdark/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samdark/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/samdark/subscriptions","organizations_url":